This paper is primarily focused on deep neural network compression for computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms for optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.AI). The paper also involves fine-tuning and knowledge distillation, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The use of compression techniques to reduce memory consumption and computation complexity is also a topic of interest in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and search algorithms, which are topics of interest in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category.
